t: Psalm 119
ALEPH.
Blessed*p are the undefiled in the way, who walk in the law of the Lord.*s
Blessed*p are they that keep his testimonies, and that seek him with the whole heart.
They*p also do no iniquity: they walk in his ways.
Thou*p hast commanded us to keep thy precepts diligently.
O*p that my ways were directed to keep thy statutes!
Then*p shall I not be ashamed, when I have respect unto all thy commandments.
I*p will praise thee with uprightness of heart, when I shall have learned thy righteous judgments.
I*p will keep thy statutes: O forsake me not utterly.
BETH.
Wherewithal*p shall a young man cleanse his way? by taking heed thereto according to thy word.
With*p my whole heart have I sought thee: O let me not wander from thy commandments.
Thy*p word have I hid in mine heart, that I might not sin against thee.
Blessed*p art thou, O Lord:*s teach me thy statutes.
With*p my lips have I declared all the judgments of thy mouth.
I*p have rejoiced in the way of thy testimonies, as much as in all riches.
I*p will meditate in thy precepts, and have respect unto thy ways.
I*p will delight myself in thy statutes: I will not forget thy word.
GIMEL.
Deal*p bountifully with thy servant, that I may live, and keep thy word.
Open*p thou mine eyes, that I may behold wondrous things out of thy law.
I*p am a stranger in the earth: hide not thy commandments from me.
My*p soul breaketh for the longing that it hath unto thy judgments at all times.
Thou*p hast rebuked the proud that are cursed, which do err from thy commandments.
Remove*p from me reproach and contempt; for I have kept thy testimonies.
Princes*p also did sit and speak against me: but thy servant did meditate in thy statutes.
Thy*p testimonies also are my delight and my counsellors.
DALETH.
My*p soul cleaveth unto the dust: quicken thou me according to thy word.
I*p have declared my ways, and thou heardest me: teach me thy statutes.
Make*p me to understand the way of thy precepts: so shall I talk of thy wondrous works.
My*p soul melteth for heaviness: strengthen thou me according unto thy word.
Remove*p from me the way of lying: and grant me thy law graciously.
I*p have chosen the way of truth: thy judgments have I laid before me.
I*p have stuck unto thy testimonies: O Lord,*s put me not to shame.
I*p will run the way of thy commandments, when thou shalt enlarge my heart.
HE.
Teach*p me, O Lord,*s the way of thy statutes; and I shall keep it unto the end.
Give*p me understanding, and I shall keep thy law; yea, I shall observe it with my whole heart.
Make*p me to go in the path of thy commandments; for therein do I delight.
Incline*p my heart unto thy testimonies, and not to covetousness.
Turn*p away mine eyes from beholding vanity; and quicken thou me in thy way.
Stablish*p thy word unto thy servant, who is devoted to thy fear.
Turn*p away my reproach which I fear: for thy judgments are good.
Behold,*p I have longed after thy precepts: quicken me in thy righteousness.
VAU.
Let*p thy mercies come also unto me, O Lord,*s even thy salvation, according to thy word.
So*p shall I have wherewith to answer him that reproacheth me: for I trust in thy word.
And*p take not the word of truth utterly out of my mouth; for I have hoped in thy judgments.
So*p shall I keep thy law continually for ever and ever.
And*p I will walk at liberty: for I seek thy precepts.
I*p will speak of thy testimonies also before kings, and will not be ashamed.
And*p I will delight myself in thy commandments, which I have loved.
My*p hands also will I lift up unto thy commandments, which I have loved; and I will meditate in thy statutes.
ZAIN.
Remember*p the word unto thy servant, upon which thou hast caused me to hope.
This*p is my comfort in my affliction: for thy word hath quickened me.
The*p proud have had me greatly in derision: yet have I not declined from thy law.
I*p remembered thy judgments of old, O Lord;*s and have comforted myself.
Horror*p hath taken hold upon me because of the wicked that forsake thy law.
Thy*p statutes have been my songs in the house of my pilgrimage.
I*p have remembered thy name, O Lord,*s in the night, and have kept thy law.
This*p I had, because I kept thy precepts.
CHETH.
Thou*p art my portion, O Lord:*s I have said that I would keep thy words.
I*p entreated thy favour with my whole heart: be merciful unto me according to thy word.
I*p thought on my ways, and turned my feet unto thy testimonies.
I*p made haste, and delayed not to keep thy commandments.
The*p bands of the wicked have robbed me: but I have not forgotten thy law.
At*p midnight I will rise to give thanks unto thee because of thy righteous judgments.
I*p am a companion of all them that fear thee, and of them that keep thy precepts.
The*p earth, O Lord,*s is full of thy mercy: teach me thy statutes.
TETH.
Thou*p hast dealt well with thy servant, O Lord,*s according unto thy word.
Teach*p me good judgment and knowledge: for I have believed thy commandments.
Before*p I was afflicted I went astray: but now have I kept thy word.
Thou*p art good, and doest good; teach me thy statutes.
The*p proud have forged a lie against me: but I will keep thy precepts with my whole heart.
Their*p heart is as fat as grease; but I delight in thy law.
It*p is good for me that I have been afflicted; that I might learn thy statutes.
The*p law of thy mouth is better unto me than thousands of gold and silver.
JOD.
Thy*p hands have made me and fashioned me: give me understanding, that I may learn thy commandments.
They*p that fear thee will be glad when they see me; because I have hoped in thy word.
I*p know, O Lord,*s that thy judgments are right, and that thou in faithfulness hast afflicted me.
Let,*p I pray thee, thy merciful kindness be for my comfort, according to thy word unto thy servant.
Let*p thy tender mercies come unto me, that I may live: for thy law is my delight.
Let*p the proud be ashamed; for they dealt perversely with me without a cause: but I will meditate in thy precepts.
Let*p those that fear thee turn unto me, and those that have known thy testimonies.
Let*p my heart be sound in thy statutes; that I be not ashamed.
CAPH.
My*p soul fainteth for thy salvation: but I hope in thy word.
Mine*p eyes fail for thy word, saying, When wilt thou comfort me?
For*p I am become like a bottle in the smoke; yet do I not forget thy statutes.
How*p many are the days of thy servant? when wilt thou execute judgment on them that persecute me?
The*p proud have digged pits for me, which are not after thy law.
All*p thy commandments are faithful: they persecute me wrongfully; help thou me.
They*p had almost consumed me upon earth; but I forsook not thy precepts.
Quicken*p me after thy lovingkindness; so shall I keep the testimony of thy mouth.
LAMED.
For*p ever, O Lord,*s thy word is settled in heaven.
Thy*p faithfulness is unto all generations: thou hast established the earth, and it abideth.
They*p continue this day according to thine ordinances: for all are thy servants.
Unless*p thy law had been my delights, I should then have perished in mine affliction.
I*p will never forget thy precepts: for with them thou hast quickened me.
I*p am thine, save me; for I have sought thy precepts.
The*p wicked have waited for me to destroy me: but I will consider thy testimonies.
I*p have seen an end of all perfection: but thy commandment is exceeding broad.
MEM.
O*p how love I thy law! it is my meditation all the day.
Thou*p through thy commandments hast made me wiser than mine enemies: for they are ever with me.
I*p have more understanding than all my teachers: for thy testimonies are my meditation.
I*p understand more than the ancients, because I keep thy precepts.
I*p have refrained my feet from every evil way, that I might keep thy word.
I*p have not departed from thy judgments: for thou hast taught me.
How*p sweet are thy words unto my taste! yea, sweeter than honey to my mouth!
Through*p thy precepts I get understanding: therefore I hate every false way.
NUN.
Thy*p word is a lamp unto my feet, and a light unto my path.
I*p have sworn, and I will perform it, that I will keep thy righteous judgments.
I*p am afflicted very much: quicken me, O Lord,*s according unto thy word.
Accept,*p I beseech thee, the freewill offerings of my mouth, O Lord,*s and teach me thy judgments.
My*p soul is continually in my hand: yet do I not forget thy law.
The*p wicked have laid a snare for me: yet I erred not from thy precepts.
Thy*p testimonies have I taken as an heritage for ever: for they are the rejoicing of my heart.
I*p have inclined mine heart to perform thy statutes alway, even unto the end.
SAMECH.
I*p hate vain thoughts: but thy law do I love.
Thou*p art my hiding place and my shield: I hope in thy word.
Depart*p from me, ye evildoers: for I will keep the commandments of my God.
Uphold*p me according unto thy word, that I may live: and let me not be ashamed of my hope.
Hold*p thou me up, and I shall be safe: and I will have respect unto thy statutes continually.
Thou*p hast trodden down all them that err from thy statutes: for their deceit is falsehood.
Thou*p puttest away all the wicked of the earth like dross: therefore I love thy testimonies.
My*p flesh trembleth for fear of thee; and I am afraid of thy judgments.
AIN.
I*p have done judgment and justice: leave me not to mine oppressors.
Be*p surety for thy servant for good: let not the proud oppress me.
Mine*p eyes fail for thy salvation, and for the word of thy righteousness.
Deal*p with thy servant according unto thy mercy, and teach me thy statutes.
I*p am thy servant; give me understanding, that I may know thy testimonies.
It*p is time for thee, Lord,*s to work: for they have made void thy law.
Therefore*p I love thy commandments above gold; yea, above fine gold.
Therefore*p I esteem all thy precepts concerning all things to be right; and I hate every false way.
PE.
Thy*p testimonies are wonderful: therefore doth my soul keep them.
The*p entrance of thy words giveth light; it giveth understanding unto the simple.
I*p opened my mouth, and panted: for I longed for thy commandments.
Look*p thou upon me, and be merciful unto me, as thou usest to do unto those that love thy name.
Order*p my steps in thy word: and let not any iniquity have dominion over me.
Deliver*p me from the oppression of man: so will I keep thy precepts.
Make*p thy face to shine upon thy servant; and teach me thy statutes.
Rivers*p of waters run down mine eyes, because they keep not thy law.
TZADDI.
Righteous*p art thou, O Lord,*s and upright are thy judgments.
Thy*p testimonies that thou hast commanded are righteous and very faithful.
My*p zeal hath consumed me, because mine enemies have forgotten thy words.
Thy*p word is very pure: therefore thy servant loveth it.
I*p am small and despised: yet do not I forget thy precepts.
Thy*p righteousness is an everlasting righteousness, and thy law is the truth.
Trouble*p and anguish have taken hold on me: yet thy commandments are my delights.
The*p righteousness of thy testimonies is everlasting: give me understanding, and I shall live.
KOPH.
I*p cried with my whole heart; hear me, O Lord:*s I will keep thy statutes.
I*p cried unto thee; save me, and I shall keep thy testimonies.
I*p prevented the dawning of the morning, and cried: I hoped in thy word.
Mine*p eyes prevent the night watches, that I might meditate in thy word.
Hear*p my voice according unto thy lovingkindness: O Lord,*s quicken me according to thy judgment.
They*p draw nigh that follow after mischief: they are far from thy law.
Thou*p art near, O Lord;*s and all thy commandments are truth.
Concerning*p thy testimonies, I have known of old that thou hast founded them for ever.
RESH.
Consider*p mine affliction, and deliver me: for I do not forget thy law.
Plead*p my cause, and deliver me: quicken me according to thy word.
Salvation*p is far from the wicked: for they seek not thy statutes.
Great*p are thy tender mercies, O Lord:*s quicken me according to thy judgments.
Many*p are my persecutors and mine enemies; yet do I not decline from thy testimonies.
I*p beheld the transgressors, and was grieved; because they kept not thy word.
Consider*p how I love thy precepts: quicken me, O Lord,*s according to thy lovingkindness.
Thy*p word is true from the beginning: and every one of thy righteous judgments endureth for ever.
SCHIN.
Princes*p have persecuted me without a cause: but my heart standeth in awe of thy word.
I*p rejoice at thy word, as one that findeth great spoil.
I*p hate and abhor lying: but thy law do I love.
Seven*p times a day do I praise thee because of thy righteous judgments.
Great*p peace have they which love thy law: and nothing shall offend them.
Lord,*sp I have hoped for thy salvation, and done thy commandments.
My*p soul hath kept thy testimonies; and I love them exceedingly.
I*p have kept thy precepts and thy testimonies: for all my ways are before thee.
TAU.
Let*p my cry come near before thee, O Lord:*s give me understanding according to thy word.
Let*p my supplication come before thee: deliver me according to thy word.
My*p lips shall utter praise, when thou hast taught me thy statutes.
My*p tongue shall speak of thy word: for all thy commandments are righteousness.
Let*p thine hand help me; for I have chosen thy precepts.
I*p have longed for thy salvation, O Lord;*s and thy law is my delight.
Let*p my soul live, and it shall praise thee; and let thy judgments help me.
I*p have gone astray like a lost sheep; seek thy servant; for I do not forget thy commandments.
